The paper investigates the randomness properties of a function that can find applications in cryptography and key distribution, indicating that it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The function is based on the divisor pairs of a natural number, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Number Theory (cs.NT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the autocorrelation properties of the function, which could be of interest to researchers in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
